/*
* Traveling salesman problem
* The book doesn't provide any psuedocode for this section.
* Main formula: p(i,L) = min[c(j,i)+p(j,L-{j})]
* p(i,L) is the cost from start node to node i after visiting nodes in list L.
* c(j,i) is the cost from node j to i, and is not the same as c(i,j) because of directed edges.
* L-{j} is list L without node j.
* 
* The book gives this example graph:
* [inf  12    11    16]
* [15   inf   15    10]
* [8    14    inf   18]
* [9    11    17   inf]
* solution for the above is p{A, {B,C,D}} (cost 44)
*
* The book also gives this example graph:
* [inf  9    inf     6]
* [8    inf   16    12]
* [14   15    inf   18]
* [7    11    19   inf]
* cost 47
*/

